l and archaeological evidence, Rough and Tumble offers a new perspective on human evolution by decoupling ideas of aggression and predation to build a more realistic understanding of what it is to be human.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFossil hominids. 0aHuman evolution. 0aHunting and gathering societies. 0aHunting, Prehistoric. 0aSocial evolution. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Physical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095512740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520955127423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520955127/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles